2.7 Layer 6: Astro-Predictive AI Engine

Innovation: Multi-cycle predictive analytics using celestial patterns

Maya astronomers achieved remarkable accuracy:

· Venus Cycle: 584-day synodic period prediction within hours
· Solar Cycle: Solar year calculation to 365.2420 days (modern: 365.2422)
· Eclipse Prediction: Saros cycle understanding
· Planetary Alignments: Multi-century event prediction

Technical Implementation:

```python
class CelestialPredictionAI:
    def __init__(self):
        self.cycles = {
            'venus': 584,
            'mars': 780,
            'jupiter': 399,
            'saturn': 378,
            'eclipse': 173,
            'sunspot': 11.3
        }
    
    def predict_urban_convergences(self, urban_data, horizon):
        """Predict rare convergence events across multiple cycles"""
        cycle_predictions = []
        for cycle_name, period in self.cycles.items():
            prediction = self.extract_cycle_component(urban_data, period)
            cycle_predictions.append((cycle_name, prediction))
        
        convergences = self.find_celestial_alignments(cycle_predictions)
        return self.rank_by_significance(convergences)
```

Urban Applications:

· Long-term infrastructure planning (20-50 year horizons)
· Climate pattern prediction for agriculture
· Energy production forecasting (solar/wind patterns)
· Economic cycle prediction for urban development

